<div class="calcpad-output">
 <!-- Showcases the variadic helpers $min$, $max$, $gcd$ and $lcm$, which accept any number of comma- or semicolon-separated arguments. -->
 <h3>Functions of multiple variables</h3>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>a</var>
   =
   <b>min</b>
   ( 2; 3; -1; 5; 7; -4 )  = -4
  </span>
  - minimum
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>b</var>
   =
   <b>max</b>
   ( 2; 3; -1; 5; 7; -4; 9; 6 )  = 9
  </span>
  - maximum
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>s</var>
   =
   <b>sum</b>
   ( 2; 3; -1; 5; 7; -4 )  = 12
  </span>
  - sum
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>s</var>
   <sub>1</sub>
   =
   <b>sumsq</b>
   ( 2; 3; -1; 5; 7; -4 )  = 104
  </span>
  - sum of squares
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>s</var>
   <sub>2</sub>
   =
   <b>srss</b>
   ( 2; 3; -1; 5; 7; -4 )  = 10.2
  </span>
  - square root of sum of squares
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>c</var>
   =
   <b>average</b>
   ( 2; 3; -1; 5; 7; -4 )  = 2
  </span>
  - average
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>p</var>
   =
   <b>product</b>
   ( 2; 3; 2; 5 )  = 60
  </span>
  - product
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>m</var>
   =
   <b>mean</b>
   ( 2; 3; 2; 5 )  = 2.78
  </span>
  - geometric mean
 </p>
 <p>
  <span class="eq">
   <var>f</var>
   (
   <var>x</var>
   )  =
   <span class="dvcs">
    <span class="c3">{</span>
    <span class="dvs">
     if
     <var>x</var>
     &lt;  ( -2 ) : 1
     <br/>
     else if
     <var>x</var>
     &gt; 4:
     <var>x</var>
     − 2
     <br/>
     else if
     <var>x</var>
     &gt; 1: 2
     <br/>
     else: -1
    </span>
   </span>
  </span>
  - selective evaluation
 </p>
